article.headline: Fordham 67, St. Bonaventure 61
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Sebastian Greene scored 18 points as Fordham extended its winning streak to five games with a 67-61 victory over St. Bonaventure on Wednesday night. Marcus Stout scored 16 points for the Rams (13-7, 6-2 Atlantic 10), who held a 31-28 lead at half. Mike Binns added 10 points and Paul Williams had 10 rebounds to go with eight points for Fordham. The winning streak is the longest for Fordham since it joined the Atlantic 10 in 1995-96. Michael Lee had 15 points and 10 rebounds to lead the Bonnies (6-15, 3-5), and Tyler Relph had 12 points. The Bonnies took a 57-55 led on a pair of free throws by Relph with 5:19 to play. Fordham scored the next 10 points, four from the line by Greene, to go up 65-57 with 37 seconds left.
